RMarkdown Class Schedule

Ken Kalbach

September 15, 2019

Class Schedule

STAT 414: Intro Prob Theory

This class is the introduction to the theory of probability in statistics, mathmatics, engineering, and other similar subjects. So far, I am enjoying the class, I like my professor and the material. I am taking this class because it is a prerequisit for many of the upper 400 level stat classes. My section meets twice a week at 9:05 am. If you want to know more about Stat 414, here’s the link. Since probability theory is heavily based in calculations, I’ve attached a photo of a tree diagram which is helpful to figure out different probabilities.

STAT 184: Introduction to R Programmaing

This class in an introduction to the coding language R. R is a statistical based coding language used by professional statisticians to analyze data. I am taking this class because I am required to take this class. So far it’s not too bad, but I know the concepts will get more complex and my frustrations with myself will grow along with the more complex topics. If you want to know more about Stat 184, here’s the link. Here is a photo of Bert and Earnie from Sesame Street holding the letter R:

Stat 462: Applied Regression Analysis

This class is an in-depth class about regression analysis. In this class I will learn about linear regression, stepwise regression, and non-linear regression models as well as correlation. I am really enjoying this class and the topics that it is covering. This class meets three times a week. If you want to learn more about the class, here’s the link.
